cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the use of technology (Deep Learning and EHR data) to improve end-of-life care, which has societal implications.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper describes the use of a Deep Neural Network to predict patient mortality and improve palliative care.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The use of EHR data and Deep Learning to improve healthcare can be considered a form of computational science and engineering.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of AI (Deep Learning) to improve healthcare outcomes.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper describes a method to improve the interaction between healthcare providers and patients by using technology to identify patients who could benefit from palliative care.
